.TH "sys_sched_setscheduler" 9 "sys_sched_setscheduler" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sys_sched_setscheduler \- set/change the scheduler policy and RT priority
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" sys_sched_setscheduler
.BI "(pid_t pid "  ","
.BI "int policy "  ","
.BI "struct sched_param __user * param "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pid" 12
the pid in question.
.IP "policy" 12
new policy.
.IP "param" 12
structure containing the new RT priority.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success. An error code otherwise.
